description:
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for friendly, self-motivated individuals to join our team of Ward Clerks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will work within a large team of experienced administrators, supporting the provision of high-quality patient care across the new Emergency Floor at the Leicester Royal Infirmary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our new, multi-million pound Emergency Floor comprises the Emergency Department (ED &amp; EDU) and Acute Medicine (Acute Assessment Units, GPAU, DVT Clinic, and General Medicine Clinics), all based at the LRI site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Emergency Floor is a very busy and demanding working environment, but the successful applicants will join a strong &amp; supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Ward Clerks work as part of a team on a 7 day, 24 hour shift pattern which requires working a mixture of days, nights and Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be required to work on their own initiative, managing their own workload, as well as being part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be computer literate, and have excellent communication &amp; customer service skills. Experience of working in an NHS environment would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A working knowledge of Track It, Nerve Centre and Patient Centre would be beneficial, however comprehensive training will be provided for all successful applicants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Davis (Admin Manager) on 0116 258 7225&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email - paul.m.davis@uhl-tr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
